<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_b466e9a9-867b-4f08-9459-429c1c2fbf8f" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="TAS"><sptc>C4D15</sptc><title id="_8002f81d-f7c8-4b59-9980-de4f89bff974">Grease trap installation in multi-storey buildings</title><archive-num>2019: H202.4i</archive-num><subclause id="_b2d52a7e-8555-4c23-90e4-7bc4869093c5" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_26c11dc9-d68b-4ced-a477-a497511d9b1c">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Grease traps in multi-storey buildings must have a reflux valve installed between the outlet and connection to the sanitary plumbing system.</p></subclause><callout id="_56390624-d745-4b44-a0b9-4d45fb4f761f"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>See <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/7756_0.3.0.xml#_97fd06e9-b2ca-4aa3-b869-d4bd9d654596" id="_5207bc67-2658-4f88-8cad-750de1603853" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">TAS Figure C4D15</xref> for a typical installation of a grease trap in a multi-storey building.</p><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/7756_0.3.0.xml" id="_97fd06e9-b2ca-4aa3-b869-d4bd9d654596" variation="TAS"><num/><title id="_18082fdd-03c9-4c67-b0de-25c9bb3e3b72"/></image-reference></callout></clause>